text: The roast pork from the roast delights shop here is good; skin is crispy, for $3.50 only. Place is also airy and spacious, with free parking slots, mainly caters to factory crowd here

This eating house is rather rundown but it offers free parking for up to 6 vehicles. The roasted chicken rice is of acceptable standard at $3.50. The milk tea was selling at $1.30.

Many stalls were closed when I visited last week during lunchtime.

Fishballs noodles and prawn mee are good. Quantity is huge too. Fresh ingredients.
Maybe good,, buy only Bangladeshi food..
The place was a little dirty. There are so many chairs and tables. But only some are suitable for sit. Remains are rust and dirty. Less food options
